# MindeesNative ‚Äî Android app (experimental)

A standalone native **Android** app built with MindeesNative. The UI is authored in
TypeScript/TSX (Atlas components + the Quantum file-based router) and runs on a real
Android view tree through an **embedded QuickJS** runtime. The native host
(`mindees-host/`) is **vendored as Kotlin source** ‚Äî no Maven dependency on
MindeesNative is required.

> **Experimental.** This scaffold is verified end-to-end in CI (the app-js bundle
> builds from npm and `gradle assembleDebug` produces an APK containing it), but the
> native mobile product is pre-1.0. Expect rough edges.

## Prerequisites

- **JDK 17**
- **Gradle 9.4.1+** (AGP 9.2 requires it) ‚Äî used once to bootstrap the wrapper
- **Android SDK** with `platforms;android-36`
- **Node 20+** (for the app-js bundle)

## Build (two phases, in order)

The native app loads `mindees-example-app/src/main/assets/mindees-app.bundle.js`,
which is **generated** from the TSX app ‚Äî it is git-ignored and absent until you build
it. Build the JS bundle **first**, then the APK:

```sh
# 1. Build the JS app bundle (installs @mindees/* from npm, runs route codegen + tsdown)
cd mindees-example-app/app-js
npm install
npm run build            # ‚Üí ../src/main/assets/mindees-app.bundle.js

# 2. Build the Android APK
cd ../..
gradle wrapper --gradle-version 9.4.1   # one-time: the wrapper jar isn't vendored
./gradlew :mindees-example-app:assembleDebug
# ‚Üí mindees-example-app/build/outputs/apk/debug/*.apk
```

Install the APK on a device/emulator with `./gradlew :mindees-example-app:installDebug`.

## Project layout

```
mindees-host/            # the native renderer + JS‚Üînative bridge ‚Äî VENDORED Kotlin source
mindees-example-app/
  app-js/                # your TypeScript/TSX app (Atlas + router); builds the JS bundle
    src/app/             # file-based routes ‚Äî drop a .tsx file to add a screen
    src/main.tsx         # entry: createNativeApp(...)
  src/main/kotlin/       # the Android host shell (MainActivity, QuickJS bridge)
```

Edit your UI under `mindees-example-app/app-js/src/`, re-run the app-js build, then
re-run `assembleDebug`.

## Notes & limitations (experimental)

- The Android package id is `dev.mindees.example` and `rootProject.name` is fixed, so
  two scaffolds can't be installed side-by-side yet (namespace parameterization is a
  planned enhancement).
- App-level Android dependencies (QuickJS, AndroidX, FlexboxLayout) still come from
  Maven Central / Google ‚Äî "no Maven" applies to the **MindeesNative host**, which is
  vendored as source.
